<br>
There's still a lot of research going on to answer the nature vs. nurture question with homosexuality, but a huge amount of evolutionary biology theory would state that it's not genetic.<br>
<br>
Why?<br>
<br>
Because genetic changes which lead to lower or nonexistant ability to reproduce by definition select themselves out.  If you had a homosexual gene, and you didn't mate, you wouldn't pass it along to your children, and pretty soon that gene would die out.  Sure, some homosexuals reproduce, but at a vastly lower rate than heterosexuals.  What you would expect to see would be a rapid dwindling of the number of homosexuals in the population, as each successive generation had fewer and fewer children born with the &quot;gene&quot;.<br>
<br>
What we see in society, however, is a pretty steady 5-10% homosexuality rate, and it's hard to say if that's a figure that is historically true (say, for the last 5000 years or so), but the rate at which a gene that led to little or no reproduction would disappear would mean that even 10 generations (300 or so years?) ago we'd have been at like 75% homosexuality to be down to 5-10% now.<br>
<br>
Clearly that wasn't the case.  So - the generic rules of evolutionary biology say that homosexuality is probably a &quot;nurture&quot; issue, not a genetic one.  That said, there is very loose evidence showing genetic differences in the brains/hormone levels/etc of homosexuals versus heterosexuals - nothing is proven yet, so for any church to come out and call it genetic would be pretty premature <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=walkabout>Walkabout</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 279<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/11/03 5:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=448.topic&index=307>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Morality is not relative.&quot;</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>That is just wrong. Our soldiers have to do what is commanded of them. Blame Bush all you want (as well you should), blame congress for defeating the constitution and giving Bush total control (as well you should), but don't blame the soldiers who are only doing as they are ordered. Many of them are against this war.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
