Original sin is in all of our genetic makeup!  Pick a sin, you'll find someone who is so drawn toward it that they &quot;can't help themselves&quot;.  It's a pathetic excuse, and attempting to label God as &quot;unfair&quot; for some reason due to it are just as pathetic.  Everyone is equally screwed here, sorry. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.visveres.myguilds.com/sigs/caledhon.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caledhontelrana>Caledhon TelRana</A> at: 3/11/03 10:34:40 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shehbahn>shehbahn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>No blood for oil!</span><br>  Posts: 691<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/11/03 10:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=448.topic&index=314>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> &gt;The fact that you do not possess a particular piece of knowledge does not of necessity invalidate the truth of that knowledge!!<br>
